Besides, I reject
the press-conference idea.

13:32.981 --> 13:34.682
You can't predict
a press conference.

13:34.716 --> 13:36.017
You can't control it.
It's a bad idea.

13:36.051 --> 13:37.418
We should tell them
we're not interested.

13:37.453 --> 13:39.487
Virginia: Yes, but when the book
does come out,

13:39.521 --> 13:41.289
I will be exposed
in front of the press,

13:41.323 --> 13:42.690
in front
of our entire readership.

13:42.724 --> 13:44.826
William:
The work speaks for itself.

13:44.860 --> 13:47.361
Uh, no, no, I'm not
discouraging, Virginia.

13:47.396 --> 13:49.564
I'm only saying
wait until after we publish.

13:49.598 --> 13:51.833
Otherwise, you'll look
like you're desperate,

13:51.867 --> 13:54.068
like you're trying to sneak
a degree in under the wire.

13:54.102 --> 13:55.536
Johnny: Leave him alone!

13:55.571 --> 13:56.871
Libby: Howie, is that a marble
in your mouth?

13:56.905 --> 13:58.372
Virginia: - "Under the wire"?
- [ Arguing continues ]

13:58.407 --> 13:59.674
Bill, that is so unfair.

13:59.708 --> 14:01.976
You know that I have been trying
to do this for years.

14:02.010 --> 14:04.445
William: I'm only trying
to point out how it appears

14:04.480 --> 14:05.680
and also reminding you

14:05.714 --> 14:08.182
that it takes all hands on deck
to launch a book.

14:08.217 --> 14:11.018
Virginia: Yes, but if I wait
until <i>after</i> publication,

14:11.053 --> 14:12.119
then it's too late.

14:12.154 --> 14:13.855
Libby: Bill,
will you grab the marble

14:13.889 --> 14:15.122
out of Howie's mouth, please?

14:15.157 --> 14:16.457
Jenny: I'm not hurting Scooter!

14:16.492 --> 14:19.527
William:
Ow! No bi-- He bit me!

14:19.561 --> 14:20.795
[ Indistinct arguing ]

14:20.829 --> 14:22.930
Libby: Howie, you can't bite.
You know that.

14:22.965 --> 14:25.666
William:
All children outside now!

14:25.701 --> 14:27.468
Johnny: - Come on, Howie.
Jenny: - Come here, boy.

14:27.503 --> 14:28.503
[ Door opens ]

14:30.606 --> 14:31.839
[ Door closes ]

14:31.874 --> 14:33.374
Libby: Let me just remind us

14:33.408 --> 14:35.743
this is one of our few weekends
together as a family,

14:35.777 --> 14:37.478
and I really
don't want it ruined

14:37.513 --> 14:39.113
with arguing and unpleasantness.

14:39.147 --> 14:40.848
Virginia:
Yes. You're right, Lib.

14:40.883 --> 14:42.550
Bill and I
will sort this out later.

14:42.584 --> 14:44.385
William: Meanwhile,
Virginia and I have

14:44.419 --> 14:46.387
a substantial amount
of work to do.

14:46.421 --> 14:48.256
Virginia: I do have
one other request, though.

14:48.290 --> 14:49.991
William: - Of?
Virginia: - Of you.

14:50.025 --> 14:54.428
I want you to talk to Tessa
about sex...

14:54.463 --> 14:57.098
About the risks
of unplanned pregnancy,

14:57.132 --> 14:59.534
about the libido
of teenage boys,

14:59.568 --> 15:03.237
you-- you, a solid
male authority figure--

15:03.272 --> 15:06.073
to put the fear of God into her.

15:07.108 --> 15:09.809
William: That is... absurd.

15:09.844 --> 15:12.245
The answer is no.

15:12.246 --> 15:14.079
Bill, she won't listen
to a word I say.

15:14.080 --> 15:15.580
Do you think that I haven't tr--

15:15.614 --> 15:18.083
Libby: I suppose, um,
George isn't up to the task?

15:18.117 --> 15:19.284
Virginia: George?

15:19.318 --> 15:21.820
No, George is sleeping
with an 18-year-old

15:21.854 --> 15:24.689
to mend his broken heart
after divorcing Audrey,

15:24.724 --> 15:25.924
so hardly the person

15:25.958 --> 15:28.159
to give sound advice
about responsible sex.

15:28.494 --> 15:30.094
William: And I am
the <i>second</i> least likely.

15:30.129 --> 15:32.096
Libby: Tessa's always been fond
of you, Bill.

15:32.131 --> 15:34.298
William:
I will not talk to Tessa!

15:34.333 --> 15:35.867
Virginia, you are her mother.

15:35.901 --> 15:37.869
You have written a book
about sex.

15:37.903 --> 15:39.737
Libby, you are her aunt,
essentially.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.973
The girl follows you around
like a puppy.

15:42.007 --> 15:43.808
I'm sure,
between the two of you,

15:43.842 --> 15:46.277
you can figure out how to talk
to a 15-year-old about sex.

15:46.311 --> 15:47.845
But what I will do is this--

15:47.880 --> 15:50.281
I will ask for peace and quiet
this weekend,

15:50.315 --> 15:52.116
no interruptions,
no distractions.

15:52.151 --> 15:55.420
I will take the same front room
I took last year

15:55.454 --> 15:57.789
in order to find
the solitude I now need

15:57.823 --> 15:59.824
to do the added work I have

15:59.858 --> 16:03.428
because Virginia has now said
she's going back to school.

16:03.462 --> 16:04.929
Libby: Tessa's in
that front room this year.

16:04.963 --> 16:09.033
William: Sh-she-- she can move.

16:10.936 --> 16:12.970
Libby: I will finish up
with the groceries.

16:13.005 --> 16:15.139
Virginia:
I will open up the back.

16:15.174 --> 16:18.543
[ Dog barking ]

16:36.128 --> 16:37.261
[ Dog barking ]

16:37.296 --> 16:39.464
William: [ Sighs ]

16:41.333 --> 16:44.435
[ Heavy breathing, moaning ]

16:52.511 --> 16:55.246
Virginia: Henry?

17:00.519 --> 17:02.820
[ Moaning continues ]

17:09.595 --> 17:11.561
Hello?!

17:11.597 --> 17:13.964
[ Moaning stops ]

17:13.999 --> 17:16.733
We're here! Hello!

17:16.769 --> 17:19.270
[ Stomping ]

17:19.304 --> 17:20.972
Hello?

17:21.006 --> 17:24.876
[ Stomping continues ]

17:24.910 --> 17:26.511
[ Door opens ]

17:26.545 --> 17:28.479
Henry: Hey.

17:28.513 --> 17:30.615
When did you get in, mom?

17:30.649 --> 17:33.084
Virginia: Uh, just now.

17:33.118 --> 17:34.318
You?

17:34.353 --> 17:36.587
Henry: You know, earlier.

17:36.622 --> 17:38.422
I'm just catching up
on some sleep.

17:39.858 --> 17:41.259
Virginia: Really?

17:44.129 --> 17:46.397
Denny: You use the phrase
"sexual tension"

17:46.431 --> 17:48.132
frequently in your book.

17:48.167 --> 17:49.801
And I think I know
what you mean by that.

17:49.835 --> 17:51.002
David: Actually, I've got

17:51.036 --> 17:52.970
"Taber's Medical Dictionary"
right here,

17:53.005 --> 17:55.907
and they don't recognize
the term "sexual tension."

17:55.941 --> 17:58.075
William: It is
the physiological elevation

17:58.110 --> 18:00.378
of sexual engagement,
Mr. Keller,

18:00.412 --> 18:01.712
usually expressed

18:01.747 --> 18:04.048
in increased blood flow
to genitals, muscle tension.

18:04.082 --> 18:05.483
Virginia: Think of it

18:05.517 --> 18:08.953
as what the body does
in response to sexual interest.

18:08.987 --> 18:12.089
And you're not going to find it
in "Taber's Dictionary"

18:12.124 --> 18:13.758
because we coined the term
ourselves.

18:13.792 --> 18:16.127
David: Uh, what in your
background, Mrs. Johnson,

18:16.161 --> 18:18.796
qualifies you to, uh,
make up new medical terms?

18:18.831 --> 18:21.032
Virginia: Well, I've spent
the last 10 years

18:21.066 --> 18:22.600
in a lab, Mr. Buckland,

18:22.634 --> 18:24.569
studying the physiology
of human sexuality--

18:24.603 --> 18:26.137
David: I meant what
in your educational background

18:26.171 --> 18:27.438
qualifies you?

18:27.472 --> 18:30.374
Dr. Masters has a BS
from, uh, Hamilton College,

18:30.409 --> 18:31.776
a medical degree from
the University of Rochester.

18:31.810 --> 18:35.346
William: While Mrs. Johnson has
obtained her BA in psychology

18:35.380 --> 18:36.814
at St. Louis University,

18:36.849 --> 18:39.917
she's also preparing for
her MA in the same subject,

18:39.952 --> 18:42.653
possibly even obtaining a PhD.

18:42.688 --> 18:43.955
Denny: You're saying

18:43.989 --> 18:45.823
you'll follow in Dr. Masters'
footsteps, Mrs. Johnson?

18:45.858 --> 18:47.491
Become a practicing physician?

18:47.526 --> 18:50.661
Virginia:
That is one possibility...

18:50.696 --> 18:52.897
among many...

18:52.931 --> 18:56.534
because if there is one thing
that our study has shown,

18:56.568 --> 18:59.604
it's that women are capable
of almost anything.

19:01.073 --> 19:03.307
Oh, well,
time for a brief break.

19:03.342 --> 19:05.142
We'll resume shortly.

19:07.646 --> 19:10.047
[ Door opens ]

19:10.082 --> 19:12.717
William: Virginia?
What happened?

19:15.554 --> 19:18.189
Open the door, Virginia.

19:18.223 --> 19:19.857
Virginia?

19:22.294 --> 19:24.328
You-- you do realize
the significance of today,

19:24.363 --> 19:27.031
perhaps the most important day
of our professional lives.

19:27.065 --> 19:31.302
Virginia: You can't talk about
my credentials like that,

19:31.336 --> 19:33.004
not in front of the press.

19:33.038 --> 19:35.406
William: They asked.
I thought you'd be grateful.

19:35.440 --> 19:36.974
I-- I rallied to your defense.

19:37.009 --> 19:38.409
Virginia:
I didn't get my degree.

19:38.443 --> 19:40.378
I haven't yet taken the final

19:40.412 --> 19:42.546
in my last remaining
statistics course.

19:42.581 --> 19:44.248
So I have not yet graduated.

19:44.283 --> 19:45.983
William: I don't understand.

19:46.018 --> 19:48.152
I-- I gave you
three months off,

19:48.186 --> 19:51.088
against every instinct
that it was a terrible idea,

19:51.123 --> 19:52.757
which it was.

19:52.791 --> 19:53.891
Virginia: And I will finish
my degree, Bill!

19:53.926 --> 19:55.960
William: For God's sake,
Virginia, calm down.

19:55.994 --> 19:58.829
Virginia: Is there not
one square inch of my life

19:58.864 --> 20:01.332
that you haven't insinuated
yourself into?

20:01.366 --> 20:04.602
I mean, my work,
my home, my bed.

20:04.636 --> 20:07.505
Can I-- can I not even have
a bathroom stall to myself?

20:07.539 --> 20:09.206
William: All right, look, I--

20:09.241 --> 20:11.342
I will accept your apology later.

20:11.376 --> 20:12.743
- For now, you have five minutes.
Virginia: - [ Scoffs ]

20:12.778 --> 20:14.979
William: And then we are--
we are going back out there,

20:15.013 --> 20:16.614
and we are continuing
this presentation

20:16.648 --> 20:19.150
like the polished
and professional researchers

20:19.184 --> 20:21.452
that we are.

20:21.486 --> 20:24.288
Five minutes, Virginia.

20:25.891 --> 20:29.160
Man: <i>As the unrest</i>
<i>in Saigon continues,</i>

20:29.194 --> 20:31.095
<i>along with Prime Minister Ky's</i>
<i>crackdown</i>

20:31.129 --> 20:33.164
<i>on the Buddhist Rebels,</i>

20:33.198 --> 20:34.532
<i>including the arrest</i>

20:34.566 --> 20:36.400
<i>of South Vietnamese</i>
<i>Buddhist leader Tri Quang.</i>

20:36.435 --> 20:37.768
<i>And now to the weather...</i>

20:37.803 --> 20:40.438
Virginia: Well, she either
climbed out the back window

20:40.472 --> 20:41.872
or she's hiding in the cellar

20:41.907 --> 20:45.343
because Henry emerged
from his room utterly alone,

20:45.377 --> 20:46.844
not a girl in sight.

20:46.878 --> 20:48.212
Jenny: It's daddy's turn.
Daddy!

20:48.246 --> 20:50.514
William:
Your mother is playing for me!

20:50.549 --> 20:51.849
Libby: Maybe he's Houdini.

20:51.883 --> 20:54.518
I mean, in less than an hour,
he picks up a local girl,

20:54.553 --> 20:57.888
seduces her under our noses,
and then makes her disappear.

20:57.923 --> 20:59.056
Virginia: That would explain

20:59.091 --> 21:00.591
how he makes
his job opportunities vanish.

21:00.625 --> 21:01.859
Jenny:
Mom, we're waiting for dad,

21:01.893 --> 21:03.728
which means
we're waiting for you.

21:03.762 --> 21:07.431
Libby: Is this, um, still the
Masters vs. The Johnsons game?

21:07.466 --> 21:11.435
Jenny: Yes.
You as dad, me, Johnny are here.

21:11.470 --> 21:12.536
Johnny: I'm not playing.

21:12.571 --> 21:16.073
Henry: Mom, Tess,
and Harry Houdini here.

21:17.309 --> 21:21.112
Libby: Anyway, uh,
I will spin the spinner.

21:21.146 --> 21:22.279
[ Clears throat ]

21:22.314 --> 21:23.881
Four.

21:23.915 --> 21:27.218
Two career cards
for your father-- naturally.

21:27.252 --> 21:28.552
"Life" imitating life.

21:28.587 --> 21:31.088
William: Is there fresh coffee?

21:31.123 --> 21:32.556
[ Spinner whirs ]

21:32.591 --> 21:35.359
Libby: Johnny, honey, will you
bring your dad some coffee?

21:35.394 --> 21:38.062
Both: Two, three,
four, five, six.

21:38.096 --> 21:40.064
Virginia: No, you cannot have
some of my cigarette.

21:40.098 --> 21:42.600
But you can keep playing
with the others.

21:42.634 --> 21:43.634
Tessa: I hate "Life."

21:43.668 --> 21:45.102
But I'll trade you,

21:45.137 --> 21:47.538
if you're insisting
I join in the family fun.

21:47.572 --> 21:48.973
Jenny: Insurance.

21:49.007 --> 21:51.342
[ Indistinct conversation ]

21:56.248 --> 21:58.449
Virginia:
All right, that's enough.

21:58.483 --> 21:59.817
That's enough.

21:59.851 --> 22:02.553
You know you can't do that
at school.

22:02.587 --> 22:03.954
You know that, right?

22:03.989 --> 22:05.956
Tessa: Yeah.

22:05.991 --> 22:08.392
Yeah.

22:08.427 --> 22:10.694
Jenny: Okay,
so, I got the 35th...

22:13.598 --> 22:15.900
William: Thank you.

22:17.869 --> 22:19.937
Johnny:
I'm not playing "Life," either.

22:19.971 --> 22:22.006
William: Well <i>you</i> should play.

22:22.040 --> 22:23.607
I have to work.

22:28.313 --> 22:31.282
Johnny: I think
they want us both to play.

22:31.316 --> 22:33.017
William: Well, you should play.

22:34.619 --> 22:37.154
It's fun.

22:37.189 --> 22:39.824
That's the--
that's the point of our--

22:39.858 --> 22:42.760
that's the point
of our time here.

22:42.794 --> 22:44.462
Johnny:
What does that even mean--

22:44.496 --> 22:46.397
"Human Sexual Response"?

22:46.431 --> 22:49.633
William: Uh, my work's
not for children, John.

22:49.668 --> 22:51.702
You know that.

22:59.678 --> 23:01.712
Johnny: [ Sighs ]

23:07.552 --> 23:10.754
[ Door creaks, closes ]

23:10.789 --> 23:12.990
William: [ Sighs ]

23:13.024 --> 23:14.892
Virginia: - Seven, eight, nine.
Jenny: - Nine.

23:14.926 --> 23:16.127
Virginia: Well, look at that.

23:16.161 --> 23:17.995
I am having children,
two children,

23:18.029 --> 23:19.530
a boy and a girl.

23:19.564 --> 23:21.966
Tessa: History doomed to repeat.

23:22.000 --> 23:23.968
Virginia: Tessie, you always
wanted a baby sister.

23:24.002 --> 23:27.738
And I, for one, am thrilled
to be having another girl--

23:27.772 --> 23:29.206
and boy, of course.

23:29.241 --> 23:30.908
Jenny: And you have to put
your kids in your car,

23:30.942 --> 23:32.409
and you have to name them.

23:32.444 --> 23:34.211
Virginia:
Well, when I was your age,

23:34.246 --> 23:36.280
my very best friend
was named Lisa Soracco,

23:36.314 --> 23:38.015
so I'm going to name
my baby girl Lisa.

23:38.049 --> 23:40.484
Jenny: And does the boy drive
an ice cream truck?

23:40.519 --> 23:41.652
Libby: [ Chuckles ]

23:41.686 --> 23:42.820
Jenny: Can you drive the truck

23:42.854 --> 23:44.488
to our house again, Henry,
please?

23:44.523 --> 23:46.390
Virginia: Speaking of,

23:46.424 --> 23:48.993
how do you not have a single
shift this weekend, Henry?

23:49.027 --> 23:50.828
Isn't this
a huge ice cream weekend?

23:50.862 --> 23:52.263
Henry: What can I say?
I'm not on the schedule.

23:52.297 --> 23:54.231
Virginia:
Well, what did Mr. Hiskey say?

23:54.266 --> 23:56.867
Both: ♪ Mr. Hiskey
likes his whiskey ♪

23:56.902 --> 23:58.736
♪ more than he likes ice cream ♪

23:58.770 --> 24:01.572
Virginia: Mr. Hiskey's
drinking issues aside,

24:01.606 --> 24:03.107
why is he reducing your hours?

24:03.141 --> 24:05.843
Henry: He's--
he's not reducing my hours.

24:05.877 --> 24:08.279
I don't work there anymore.

24:08.313 --> 24:11.115
Libby: Uh, Tessa and I made,
this afternoon, of all things,

24:11.149 --> 24:12.349
a lingonberry pie--

24:12.384 --> 24:13.817
Virginia:
This was not the agreement.

24:13.852 --> 24:16.554
We agreed that you could defer
college for one year

24:16.588 --> 24:18.122
for gainful employment only.

24:18.156 --> 24:19.623
Henry: And I've had three jobs.

24:19.658 --> 24:21.058
Virginia:
And you've lost three jobs.

24:21.092 --> 24:22.359
I don't underst--

24:22.394 --> 24:24.595
How could you get fired
from driving an ice cream truck?

24:24.629 --> 24:25.729
It was-- what?

24:25.764 --> 24:28.332
It was too challenging,
intellectually?

24:28.366 --> 24:29.900
Or too cold?

24:29.935 --> 24:31.168
Henry: I wasn't fired.
I quit.

24:31.203 --> 24:33.571
Virginia: [ Exhales sharply ]

24:33.605 --> 24:36.707
Um, whipped cream, please,
on my pie.

24:36.741 --> 24:42.446
Libby: And you have never tasted
a crust so buttery and flaky.

24:42.480 --> 24:44.014
Virginia: I don't understand
about the job--

24:44.049 --> 24:47.685
about the jobs--
why you keep losing them.

24:47.719 --> 24:50.187
Henry: Maybe you just
don't understand <i>me.</i>

24:50.222 --> 24:53.724
♪ Mr. Hiskey, feeling risky ♪

24:53.758 --> 24:55.759
Both: ♪ took his ice cream truck
for a spin ♪

24:55.794 --> 24:56.927
Jenny: [ Giggles ]

24:56.962 --> 24:58.629
[ Crickets chirping ]

24:59.063 --> 25:00.631
[ Knock on door ]

25:00.665 --> 25:01.932
[ Door opens ]

25:01.966 --> 25:03.467
Libby: Making any progress?

25:03.501 --> 25:05.969
William: Uh, slow progress,
glacially slow.

25:06.004 --> 25:08.872
Libby: Well, um,
Tessa needs the room now.

25:08.906 --> 25:10.641
Everybody's headed to bed.

25:10.675 --> 25:12.009
William:
Sh-she can sleep with Henry.

25:12.043 --> 25:13.977
Libby: They're too old,
they say,

25:14.012 --> 25:16.980
meaning they're self-conscious
about boy/girl issues.

25:17.015 --> 25:18.815
William: This--
this is my work space.

25:18.850 --> 25:20.217
Libby: During the day.

25:20.251 --> 25:21.985
And for sleeping, you will
have to head back to our room.

25:22.020 --> 25:25.155
William: That-- that is, uh...

25:25.189 --> 25:30.460
Uh, the mattress in that room
dates back to the Confederacy.

25:30.495 --> 25:33.263
You remember last time.
My back spasmed for weeks.

25:33.297 --> 25:34.698
Libby: Bill, all of the rooms
are spoken for.

25:34.732 --> 25:36.400
There is a spare mattress.

25:36.434 --> 25:39.002
You could drag it
into the living room.

25:39.037 --> 25:43.407
William: The living room
is overrun... with people.

25:43.441 --> 25:47.644
Libby: Well, those are
your only options, I'm afraid.

25:47.679 --> 25:49.179
William: Fine.

25:52.250 --> 25:57.320
I will take the, uh, chaise
in the backyard instead.

25:57.355 --> 25:59.322
Libby:
You're gonna sleep outside.

25:59.357 --> 26:01.925
William: Under the stars, yes.

26:01.959 --> 26:03.760
Isn't that the, uh--

26:03.795 --> 26:06.530
isn't that the point
of a vacation, yeah?

26:06.564 --> 26:08.298
[ Inhales deeply ]

26:08.332 --> 26:09.833
Enjoying fresh air...

26:09.867 --> 26:13.704
Communing with nature.

26:13.738 --> 26:17.441
[ Crickets chirping ]

26:17.475 --> 26:19.609
[ Owl hooting ]

26:26.951 --> 26:28.285
William: [ Sighs ]

26:28.319 --> 26:30.320
[ Dog barking ]

26:47.872 --> 26:49.873
[ Insect buzzing ]

26:49.907 --> 26:51.775
[ Buzzing stops ]

26:53.778 --> 26:55.045
[ Buzzing resumes ]

26:55.079 --> 26:56.213
[ Birds chirping ]

26:56.247 --> 26:57.514
Jenny:
It's what they do in Hawaii.

26:57.548 --> 26:59.616
- It's called a powwow.
Johnny: - It's a luau.

26:59.650 --> 27:01.852
And Howie and I think
it's stupid,

27:01.886 --> 27:02.886
