36:02.126 --> 36:03.893
Virginia: Serax?

36:03.928 --> 36:06.963
For anxiety?
For, uh, depression?

36:06.997 --> 36:09.065
Libby: I just I keep
thinking about the South

36:09.100 --> 36:10.433
- and how--
Virginia: - The South?

36:10.468 --> 36:12.669
Libby:
How dangerous it's become.

36:12.703 --> 36:14.671
Over 30 people
have lost their lives--

36:14.705 --> 36:16.272
did you know that?--

36:16.307 --> 36:21.311
Fighting for Dr. King's cause,
fighting for basic human rights.

36:21.345 --> 36:26.649
Virginia: 30 is--
it's a shocking number, but...

36:26.684 --> 36:28.785
Libby: [ Crying ]

36:28.819 --> 36:32.122
Virginia:
Perhaps there are better ways

36:32.156 --> 36:35.325
to process the daily news
besides drugs.

36:36.927 --> 36:38.528
Libby: Yeah.

36:38.562 --> 36:40.396
[ Sniffles ]

36:40.431 --> 36:42.165
I suppose you're right.
I--

36:42.199 --> 36:44.300
[ Chuckles, sniffles ]

36:44.335 --> 36:46.236
Life is filled with loss.

36:46.270 --> 36:49.873
It is ridiculous
to think that you can stop it.

36:51.709 --> 36:53.409
Virginia: Right.

36:56.814 --> 37:00.383
David: Your data seems
to support a societal trend,

37:00.417 --> 37:03.419
the double standard between men
and women that's vanishing,

37:03.454 --> 37:04.754
the "thou shalt nots"

37:04.788 --> 37:07.457
replaced with "thou shalt
jump into bed with whomevers,"

37:07.491 --> 37:11.961
meaning, with your emphasis
on female sexual pleasure,

37:11.996 --> 37:15.365
can a woman feel free now
to say no?

37:15.399 --> 37:17.734
William: Of course she can.

37:17.768 --> 37:19.335
Virginia: She absolutely can.

37:19.370 --> 37:22.705
Our study gives women more
freedom than ever to say no

37:22.740 --> 37:25.275
because a woman will no longer
be making her decisions

37:25.309 --> 37:26.643
out of fear.

37:26.677 --> 37:30.079
She-- Yes, Miss Delacourt?
<i>Ladies' Home Journal?</i>

37:30.114 --> 37:31.848
Carole: Yes, ma'am, um...

37:31.882 --> 37:35.151
I assume when you say "fear,"
Mrs. Johnson,

37:35.186 --> 37:37.387
you mean the traditional fears

37:37.421 --> 37:40.657
women have always had to
contend with regarding sex--

37:40.691 --> 37:44.127
fear of disease,
social ostracism,

37:44.161 --> 37:46.262
pregnancy,
the biggest fear of all?

37:46.297 --> 37:47.897
Virginia: Yes.

37:47.932 --> 37:50.166
[ Clears throat ]
Yes, all stemming from--

37:50.201 --> 37:51.935
William: Stemming from
sexual ignorance.

37:51.969 --> 37:53.236
Sexual know-how means

37:53.270 --> 37:56.339
a woman now will have
a more sophisticated choice

37:56.373 --> 37:58.708
because it is <i>her</i> choice.

37:58.742 --> 38:00.176
Virginia: Yes?

38:00.211 --> 38:02.679
Peter: Peter Norris,
<i>New York Times.</i>

38:02.713 --> 38:05.248
So, is it possible,
as some clergy predict,

38:05.282 --> 38:08.117
that the elimination of fear
will break down all barriers,

38:08.152 --> 38:09.552
including barriers

38:09.587 --> 38:12.589
that protect us from disease,
stigma, unwanted pregnancy?

38:12.623 --> 38:14.123
David: Exactly my point.

38:14.158 --> 38:16.626
Virginia: That depends what you
mean by "barriers," Mr. Norris.

38:16.660 --> 38:17.927
David: What do you mean
by "barriers"?

38:17.962 --> 38:19.329
William: There is no universe

38:19.363 --> 38:21.397
where fear is a barrier
worth preserving.

38:21.432 --> 38:22.699
David: Dr. Masters,
you don't believe

38:22.733 --> 38:26.102
people should be bound
by any societal convention?

38:26.136 --> 38:27.437
William: You can misquote me
however you--

38:27.471 --> 38:29.239
Virginia: We do believe
in many social conventions,

38:29.273 --> 38:30.873
and we are seeing
plenty of evidence

38:30.908 --> 38:32.175
that young men and women today

38:32.209 --> 38:34.077
are inclined
to work things out emotionally

38:34.111 --> 38:36.446
rather than fixating on sex,
per se.

38:36.480 --> 38:38.481
So, no.

38:38.515 --> 38:40.650
No, we do not believe
that the removal of fear

38:40.684 --> 38:42.418
leads to the destruction
of good values.

38:42.453 --> 38:44.621
William: I believe
whatever the arrangement

38:44.655 --> 38:46.422
between grown,
consenting adults,

38:46.457 --> 38:49.792
it must begin with the truth.

38:53.130 --> 38:55.164
Tessa: You want a drink?

38:55.199 --> 38:57.433
William: Uh,
the coffee will be ready soon.

38:59.169 --> 39:01.137
Tessa: A grown-up drink.

39:07.811 --> 39:10.446
William: [ Sniffs ]

39:10.481 --> 39:13.316
